{
  "stem": "15732.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think the next day or the day after we were put on a train again.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that would-- would be the hardest thing to cross, and that was Linz, to go on to Linz.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In Linz, there was the so-- so to speak, the border of the Russian empire.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You see, when they conquered half of Europe, it took them a long while until they completely retreated.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Part of Austria remained under the Russian occupation, so to speak, for long, long years until the Russian retreated.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in Linz was the place that the Americans took over.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The Russian stopped.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it was the real border between Russia and America, or Russia-- it was American part of Austria.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[SIGHS] There it was a little bit more complicated already, because there they had somehow-- we had a new leader, that means I called him leader, that young man, a very nice young man, who told us you go on that train and I have-- he had most probably a paper that this group he can take on the other side.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "A common--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hard to speak.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Between 20 and 30, I would say.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "While we were-- there we are talking about going on a train, we are talking only about cattle wagons, because there were no private, no first class or second class.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were all cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We mounting those cattle wagons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when we approached a station that was near the border, that was a station in which the Russian went from-- from wagon to wagon to see-- to count who is going, what is going.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Suddenly we heard that alle raus in German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Everybody should come out.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
